import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    age_group_counts = data.groupby('age_group')['people'].sum()
    age_group_counts.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'orange', 'green', 'red', 'purple'])
    
    plt.title('What is the distribution of people by age group?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Age Group')
    plt.ylabel('Number of People')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Age Groups'])
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_pivot = data.pivot_table(index='age_group', columns='sex', values='people', aggfunc='sum')
    data_pivot.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    
    plt.title('How does the number of people vary by sex?')
    plt.xlabel('Age Group')
    plt.ylabel('Number of People')
    plt.legend(title='Sex')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    
    yearly_data = data.groupby('year')['people'].sum().reset_index()
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.plot(yearly_data['year'], yearly_data['people'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of People')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend in the number of people over the years?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    
    data_grouped = data.groupby(['year', 'age_group'])['people'].sum().unstack()
    
    data_grouped.plot(kind='area', stacked=True)
    plt.title("What is the age distribution of the population over the years?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Year")
    plt.ylabel("Number of People")
    plt.legend(title="Age Group", loc="upper left")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['age_group'] = pd.cut(data['age'], bins=[0, 18, 35, 50, 65, 100], labels=['0-18', '19-35', '36-50', '51-65', '66+'])
    data_grouped = data.groupby(['year', 'age_group', 'sex'])['people'].sum().unstack().reset_index()
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    for sex in data['sex'].unique():
        sex_data = data_grouped[data_grouped['sex'] == sex]
        ax.bar(sex_data['age_group'], sex_data['people'], label=sex)
    
    ax.set_xlabel('Age Group')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of People')
    ax.set_title('How does the age distribution of the population vary by sex?')
    ax.legend(title='Sex')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
